---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import TypingAnimation from '../components/TypingAnimation.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="Alexandra Kelstrom is a software engineer, responsible AI advocate, and the person behind codewizwit. From bartender to AI enablement leader, this is the story."
>
  <article class="about">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="about-hero section-cream section" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
      <div class="container about-hero-inner">
        <img
          src="/images/image.webp"
          alt="Alexandra Kelstrom portrait"
          class="about-portrait"
          width="560"
          height="747"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <div>
          <p class="label label-gold">Hello world, I'm Alexandra.</p>
          <h1 id="about-heading" class="about-title">
            The wiz who dove in sideways.
          </h1>
          <p class="about-lede">
            AI Enablement Engineer, responsible AI advocate, and living proof that
            the path doesn't have to be straight.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 1: The Story -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="act1-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label label-gold">Act I</p>
        <h2 id="act1-heading">The story</h2>
        <div class="act1-layout">
          <div class="prose">
            <p>
              With roots in Chicago, I lived in six different countries outside
              the US: Taiwan, Latvia, Czech Republic, England, Scotland, and Poland.
              That kind of movement taught me how to read rooms fast and adapt
              to anything.
            </p>
            <p>
              I studied Media and Design at DePaul University in Chicago, then
              bartended for ten years before getting into tech. The service
              industry taught me empathy as an operational skill: reading
              people, understanding needs, and solving problems in real-time.
            </p>
            <p>
              Then COVID hit. I got furloughed. Instead of waiting for the
              world to fix itself, I invested my life savings in the UPenn
              LPS Coding Bootcamp. Night after night, I broke things,
              rebuilt them, and kept going. The hard work paid off when I
              got my first Software Engineer job offer the day I graduated.
            </p>
            <p>
              I walked into tech carrying everything those years had taught me.
              Turns out, empathy and adaptability translate pretty well to
              engineering.
            </p>
          </div>
          <figure class="about-door">
            <img
              src="/images/door.jpg"
              alt="Red door with stenciled city names: Chicago, Gdansk, Riga, Taipei and others"
              width="998"
              height="1734"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>The doors that led me here</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 2: The Work -->
    <section class="section-dark section" aria-labelledby="act2-heading">
      <div class="container act2-layout">
        <div>
          <p class="label about-dark-label">Act II</p>
          <h2 id="act2-heading" class="about-dark-heading">The work</h2>
          <div class="prose about-dark-prose">
            <p>
              Coming straight out of a bootcamp to my first job as a junior
              dev, impostor syndrome was real and the learning curve was steep.
              I learned everything on the job while building: micro-services,
              cloud infrastructure, automated testing. And that
              became a fundamental rhythm of how I work: building expertise
              while driving outcomes.
            </p>
            <p>
              That rhythm never stopped. I was always learning, always
              building. So when ChatGPT dropped in late 2022, it opened my
              world. As someone with more ideas than hours in the day, I could
              direct AI to execute my vision, my way, 100x faster. It made me feel like a boss. But the tension hit just as fast:
              if AI can do this, what happens to the people?
            </p>
            <p>
              This question changed the direction of my career as generative
              AI was going mainstream. I believed in what AI could do and wanted to share that. But
              I couldn't ignore its impact on people. So I set out to make
              responsible AI something tangible for engineers. I built
              frameworks, shipped code, ran experiments, and started writing
              and speaking publicly about it. That became the groundwork
              for my brand, and the idea of "No Human Left Behind."
            </p>
            <p>
              Now, as an AI Enablement Engineer, I help teams evolve with
              AI: shifting left, encoding with intent, managing context. But
              the harder part is building trust and guiding people through the
              mental shift that makes everything click. At the end of the day,
              it's coaching, building, and reading the room.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figure class="act2-figure">
          <img
            src="/images/ai-summit.jpeg"
            alt="Alexandra at AI Summit New York, placing a tile on an interactive pixel art wall"
            class="act2-photo"
            width="768"
            height="1024"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>AI Summit NY 2025, Future AI Leader</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 3: Beyond the Code -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="act3-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label label-gold">Act III</p>
        <h2 id="act3-heading">Beyond the code</h2>
        <div class="beyond-grid">
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Soundtrack</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Huge music nerd. Soul, jazz, R&amp;B, rock, oldies, reggae, indie. Hip-hop and doo-wop are my favorites. Always loud.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Fuel</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Total foodie. Good meals start the best conversations. Great snacks fuel the best ideas.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Fiction</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Sci-fi. Always pondering the future we're building.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Eye</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">DePaul Media &amp; Design grad. Visual thinker solving technical problems.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Superpower</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Empathy. Understanding people, anticipating needs, and turning that into strategic problem solving. The bartender instinct never left.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Roots</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">
              Home is where my head is. Chicago bred, Philly based. Dual citizen
              (US &amp; EU). Lived in six countries outside the US.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Hot Dog -->
    <section class="section-gold section" aria-labelledby="hot-dog-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="hot-dog-heading" class="hot-dog-section-title">
          And yes, <a href="/the-hot-dog" class="link"><TypingAnimation static="" typed="the hot dog is a whole thing." id="hotdog-about" /></a>
        </h2>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .about-portrait {
    width: clamp(180px, 22vw, 280px);
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 15%;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .about-lede {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 36rem;
  }

  .act1-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-door {
    position: sticky;
    top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-door img {
    width: 280px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }


  .act2-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr clamp(300px, 36vw, 440px);
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .act2-figure {
    padding-top: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .act2-photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  .about figcaption {
    margin-top: var(--space-3xs);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .section-dark figcaption {
    color: var(--color-gray-light);
  }

  .about-dark-label {
    color: var(--color-gray-light);
  }

  .about-dark-heading {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .about-dark-prose {
    color: var(--color-gray-light);
  }

  .section-gold.section:has(.hot-dog-section-title) {
    padding-block: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .hot-dog-section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-black);
  }

  .hot-dog-section-title .link {
    color: var(--color-black);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-black);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
  }

  .hot-dog-section-title .link:hover {
    color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.7);
  }

  .hot-dog-section-title :global(.typing-cursor) {
    background-color: var(--color-black);
  }

  .about .prose a {
    color: var(--color-gold-dark);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .about .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-gold-hover);
  }

  .section-dark .prose a {
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .section-dark .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .beyond-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .beyond-item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-gray-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .beyond-label {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xs);
  }

  .beyond-text {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-hero-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .about-portrait {
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .about-lede {
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .act1-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-door {
      text-align: center;
      position: static;
    }

    .about-door img {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 360px;
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .act2-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .act2-figure {
      text-align: center;
      padding-top: 0;
    }

    .act2-photo {
      max-width: 280px;
      margin-inline: auto;
      position: static;
    }

    .beyond-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .beyond-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
